pageTitle: Re: Too much...: Nikon FX SLR (DF, D1-D4, D600-D800) Talk Forum: Digital Photography Review
textBeforeTable: Flat view Next unread Next Previous First Parent Forum Complain Reply   Reply with quote   I just don't get how CA is such a big deal with photographers. It's just a bit of purple tinging. I love spectro green tinges personally that can appear with fast lenses. That said, I have noticed that people loose sleep over the wrong things in this forum. Almost all of them. Look at the edge of the buildings, the poles, the tree leaves, the pillars in shot 4, the buildings in shot 12...it's all over the place. How can you not see all the CA. I also see too much halo action happening here (over sharpening)...otherwise
